rComments: Érik is a really nice guy and his first time teaching Génétique might be seen as a disaster, but it wasn't that bad. He cares and wants to help, hence him repeating his explanation often in class. His exams are VERY easy, if you do the problems in the manual!! You can find them online, thus no need for the textbook! Funny guy and very chill class

His first time teaching the class so it was very unorganized, which is to be expected but went beyond that. Curved tests by 15% because the class average was in the 50s. The textbook was lifesaving and contained many practice questions. Would have been nice to have recommended exercises though because each chapter had over 100 questions.

He's not the usual prof for this class and he thought the old prof would allow him to use his notes but about 2 weeks into the semester, he got an e-mail from the other prof saying he was not allowed to use his notes. So obviously he had ppts with some typos and they were posted late because he was making them LIVE. Great prof, cares for ur success

He's a nice guy for sure. He consistently tells us to sit down and do problems from the book, and those are the problems that appear on the test (and the textbook problems on the test aren't even the challenge problems). Clear expectations, and curves tests by 15 %. He could explain things better, but he knows this and explains twice when necessary

À éviter. Il finit souvent ses présentation à 4h du matin et ça se voit, car il y a beaucoup de fautes. Pour un cours comme génétique, les typos font une grande différence. Les examens sont beaucoup plus difficiles que la matière étudiée en classe.
